Gnome Subtitles
=============================
http://gnome-subtitles.sf.net


RELEASE PROCEDURE
=================

	1.  Revise base project files
	2.  Set shell variables
	3.  Commit changes and tag
	4.  Copy SubLib
	5.  Create source package
	6.  Create screenshots
	7.  Release sources
	8.  Update websites
	9.  Notify
	10. Packages


1. Revise base project files
============================

	- CREDITS
	- README
	- NEWS
	- TODO
	- configure.in: ACINIT
	- ChangeLog using svn2log:
		svn log -v --xml https://gnome-subtitles.svn.sf.net/svnroot/gnome-subtitles/trunk/gnome-subtitles | svn2log.py -s -O -H -p '/(branches/[^/]+|trunk)/' -o ChangeLog


2. Set shell variables
======================

	- GS_VERSION="0.1"


3. Commit changes and tag
=========================

	- Commit changes for the release
	- Tag the release with (replace VERSION):
		svn copy https://gnome-subtitles.svn.sf.net/svnroot/gnome-subtitles/trunk/gnome-subtitles https://gnome-subtitles.svn.sf.net/svnroot/gnome-subtitles/tags/gnome-subtitles-$GS_VERSION -m "Tagging the $GS_VERSION release."
	- Check new version in:
		http://svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/gnome-subtitles/tags/


4. Copy SubLib
==============

	- Extract the latest SubLib sources to the project dir
	- Delete all files inside sublib/docs


5. Create source package
========================

	- Autogen autotools files with:
		autogen.sh
	- Package with:
		make dist
	- Test package with:
		tar xzf gnome-subtitles-$GS_VERSION.tar.gz && cd gnome-subtitles-$GS_VERSION && ./configure && make


6. Create Screenshots
=====================

	- Screenshots are to be created only if any of the windows/dialogs' aspect changes
	- Create screenshots with:
		gnome-screenshot --window --include-border --delay=5 --border-effect=shadow
	- Flatten images with white background
	- Screenshots for sf.net project page:
		- Rescale to maximum 640x480 with cubic method
		- Sharpen with a factor of 25


7. Release sources
===================

	- Add to File Release System in Sourceforge
	- Verify integrity
	- Build the source package using the "Test package with" commands above


8. Update websites
==================

	- Gnome Subtitles website:
		About
		Download
		Screenshots
	- Sourceforge project page:
		Summary
		Screenshots
	- Freshmeat project page
		Release
		Project info
		Screenshot
	- Gnome Files page


9. Notify
=========

	- Gnome Subtitles News
	- Update the Sourceforge project news
	- Send Email Release Notice in the File Release System
	- Send mail to the Gnome Announce mailing list
	- Send mail to the Gnome Subtitles mailing list
	- Send mail to the Mono Announce mailing list
	- Update threads in distro's forums

10. Packages
============

	- Make changes to the Gentoo ebuild
	- Notify packagers
